leave him there?

00:41.737 --> 00:43.608
The cops shut us down for
more than a couple of days.

00:43.652 --> 00:45.088
The mill won't survive that!

00:45.132 --> 00:46.350
There was a cancellation
last minute.

00:46.394 --> 00:48.918
The specs on one of
the crates was off.

00:48.961 --> 00:51.181
Don't they check the specs way
earlier than the last minute?

00:51.225 --> 00:53.879
Like, before it's packed?JAKE: I had a good day.

00:53.923 --> 00:55.229
CASS: What's a good day
for a detective?

00:55.272 --> 00:58.101
Mm! Mm.

00:58.145 --> 01:00.103
The mystery order is back, baby.

01:00.147 --> 01:03.715
GARRETT: I got to, like,
live with that shit,

01:03.759 --> 01:05.108
the rest of my life.

01:25.259 --> 01:27.261
♪

01:51.328 --> 01:53.330
♪

02:23.360 --> 02:25.362
♪

02:58.482 --> 03:00.441
$9.67.

03:12.540 --> 03:15.151
Sh... I'm sorry, I'm short.Yeah, I...

03:15.195 --> 03:19.808
JENNY:
Here. Give me your four.

03:19.851 --> 03:21.244
Are you sure?

03:21.288 --> 03:22.898
: Oh, my God,
thank you so much.

03:22.941 --> 03:26.641
JENNY:
Of course.

03:26.684 --> 03:29.034
Looks like
it's going to a good cause.

03:30.688 --> 03:31.820
Yeah.

03:31.863 --> 03:33.909
Here you go.

03:35.911 --> 03:37.869
Thanks.

03:40.524 --> 03:43.353
And the prescriptions
they set aside.

03:45.355 --> 03:46.965
Thanks.

03:47.009 --> 03:48.793
ETTA: Got a new baby
coming next week,

03:48.837 --> 03:50.273
most likely.

03:50.317 --> 03:52.493
Etta, how are you
gonna manage a baby?

03:52.536 --> 03:54.408
The same way I managed
when you were here.

03:54.451 --> 03:56.236
Big ones help
with the little ones.

03:56.279 --> 03:57.628
How it's always been.

03:57.672 --> 03:59.891
So you tell mea story.

03:59.935 --> 04:01.850
Got a fella?

04:01.893 --> 04:05.027
Just cleaning. But I'm good.

04:05.070 --> 04:07.072
Uh, I start
a new place next week.

04:07.116 --> 04:09.031
Real big house. Five bedrooms.

04:09.074 --> 04:11.729
Some real estate guy.What?

04:11.773 --> 04:13.862
See, that makes me happy,
to see my kids

04:13.905 --> 04:15.690
doing good out in the world.

04:15.733 --> 04:17.692
And your education?

04:17.735 --> 04:19.868
Uh, I have some things
in the works.

04:19.911 --> 04:21.870
Mm-hmm.

04:21.913 --> 04:24.394
I need money for my lunch.

04:24.438 --> 04:25.961
Excuse me?Please.

04:26.004 --> 04:28.311
I need money for my lunch,
please, Miss Etta.

04:28.355 --> 04:30.052
What's wrong with the food
we got here?

04:30.095 --> 04:31.619
I'm out mowing lawns.

04:31.662 --> 04:33.316
I don't have time
to come home between.

04:33.360 --> 04:34.665
JENNY:
Can I give him a few?

04:34.709 --> 04:36.624
ETTA:
Lookie there.

04:36.667 --> 04:39.931
Miss Jenny want to give you
her hard-earned money.

04:39.975 --> 04:42.238
Well, I'm not going to let her.

04:42.282 --> 04:43.413
JEREMY:
Figures.

04:43.457 --> 04:44.936
ETTA:
"Figures"?

04:44.980 --> 04:46.634
You need to be working
on them math figures,

04:46.677 --> 04:48.592
instead of running
that sass mouth.

04:48.636 --> 04:51.421
Get out of here
before I wear you out.

04:52.988 --> 04:54.424
That's nice of you,
Miss Jenny.

04:54.468 --> 04:55.860
But that one there?

04:55.904 --> 04:58.341
He needs to learn
to do with less.

04:58.385 --> 05:00.517
He comes from money?

05:00.561 --> 05:02.998
No, he comes from alcoholics,
just like most of y'all.

05:05.261 --> 05:07.872
So the extra roll Bud canceled
the night of Seven Bloods

05:07.916 --> 05:09.221
is rescheduled for tomorrow.

05:09.265 --> 05:12.050
Hmm.

05:12.094 --> 05:14.009
I can't do that, Jake.

05:14.052 --> 05:15.837
Judge Richards is not
gonna give me a warrant

05:15.880 --> 05:18.056
to search on mill property.
Where does it go after that?

05:18.100 --> 05:20.320
I followed it.
It goes through a train depot,

05:20.363 --> 05:22.147
then straight on to Canada.

05:22.191 --> 05:25.412
Okay, well, we'll have
to find some other way, then.

05:25.455 --> 05:27.631
Oh, for fuck's sake. Tell the
judge a confidential informant--

05:27.675 --> 05:29.764
that's me, by the way...Let me finish.

05:29.807 --> 05:31.722
Why can't you ever let me
finish a goddamn thought

05:31.766 --> 05:33.637
before you jump down my throat

05:33.681 --> 05:35.378
Jesus Christ, I'm-a pass out
if I have to listen

05:35.422 --> 05:37.554
to every step
of your master fucking...Hey. I realize that

05:37.598 --> 05:40.557
you pride yourself on using
a fucking hammer for everything.

05:40.601 --> 05:42.820
But some things
require a scalpel.

05:46.998 --> 05:50.045
What?
Come on. Just like
old times, huh?

05:52.090 --> 05:53.657
Man, fuck you.Mm, you know.

05:56.617 --> 05:59.228
Here's what I can do.

05:59.271 --> 06:03.232
I can go to the judge
and tell him a C.I. has told me

06:03.275 --> 06:05.234
that there's a connection
between mill activity

06:05.277 --> 06:06.670
and the night the blood
was found,

06:06.714 --> 06:08.193
and we need to search the mill.

06:08.237 --> 06:10.370
The shipment goes out at,
what, 10:00 p.m.?

06:10.413 --> 06:12.110
Uh So that means

06:12.154 --> 06:14.330
the shipment will be ready
in the mill by the afternoon,

06:14.374 --> 06:17.420
we show up at 3:00 p.m.
with a warrant, and...

06:17.464 --> 06:19.074
The roll is sitting there.

06:19.117 --> 06:21.946
The warrant covers the mill
and everything in it.

06:21.990 --> 06:24.253
Genius.

06:24.296 --> 06:27.299
Well, I'm still not sure Bud
Carl's involved, but I sure hope

06:27.343 --> 06:29.301
this shuts you the
hell up about it.Hmm. Hmm.

06:29.345 --> 06:30.825
So what's say I get a coffee
in here, or something?

06:30.868 --> 06:33.610
I can't seem to find my mug.

06:53.587 --> 06:55.545
BUD: It wasn't
just back there,

06:55.589 --> 06:57.373
there's one on
the front door, too.GOOT: All right.

06:57.417 --> 06:59.114
So you tell them
I don't need the threats.

06:59.157 --> 07:03.988
And if it's not them, I want
to know who the fuck it is.

07:04.032 --> 07:06.251
I'm so sorry. I didn't know
you were gonna be home.

07:06.295 --> 07:08.079
I'll get in touch with them.

07:08.123 --> 07:10.647
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.
Okay. Thanks.

07:10.691 --> 07:12.127
How you doing?Hmm.

07:18.481 --> 07:20.962
Sorry about that.

07:21.005 --> 07:25.619
I'm gonna be working home
most of the day, so, uh,

07:25.662 --> 07:27.751
no need to do the office.
I'll redd up in there.

07:27.795 --> 07:29.405
Okay.

07:29.449 --> 07:31.015
The laundries
are in a hamper,

07:31.059 --> 07:34.236
the-the soap and that you asked
for is on the counter.

07:34.279 --> 07:36.020
Thanks.

07:40.590 --> 07:43.724
One other thing.

07:51.079 --> 07:54.691
Careful.

07:54.735 --> 07:56.911
What happened?

07:56.954 --> 07:58.521
Going to work, come out here,

07:58.565 --> 08:00.958
there's blood all
over everywhere.

08:01.002 --> 08:02.394
Blood?Oh, no, no, no.

08:02.438 --> 08:05.659
It's... paint.

08:05.702 --> 08:07.965
What

08:08.009 --> 08:10.359
Well, it's a prank, you know?

08:10.402 --> 08:12.143
Environmental activist.

08:12.187 --> 08:14.363
Loons hate me
'cause I own a steel mill.

08:14.406 --> 08:16.147
It's happened before.

08:16.191 --> 08:17.366
Anyhow,

08:17.409 --> 08:19.629
I tried cleaning up
best I could,

08:19.673 --> 08:21.283
but nothing helped. You
think you can go over

08:21.326 --> 08:23.807
to Giant Eagle, get a
carpet cleaning machine?

08:23.851 --> 08:25.461
You know, take a pass?

08:25.505 --> 08:27.332
Course.

08:30.466 --> 08:32.033
Um...

08:32.076 --> 08:34.557
Yinz doing okay, these days?

08:34.601 --> 08:37.560
Yeah. Yeah, I, I signed up

08:37.604 --> 08:39.562
for that data processing class
I told you about.

08:39.606 --> 08:41.999
Ah, that's great.

08:42.043 --> 08:45.525
I hope you'll let me know
if you need anything.

08:45.568 --> 08:47.004
Seriously,
anything you need.

09:06.633 --> 09:08.243
Good morning, Elaine.

09:08.286 --> 09:09.984
Hey, Pete.
Hey.

09:10.027 --> 09:12.987
This is, uh, Toni Douglas,
recently joined the Braden PD.

09:13.030 --> 09:14.162
RICHARDS:
Pete.

09:14.205 --> 09:17.252
Come on in.

09:22.083 --> 09:23.737
RICHARDS: How are
Joan and the baby?

09:23.780 --> 09:26.087
Take a load off,
Officer Douglas.

09:26.130 --> 09:29.133
Thank you, ma'am.TRASK: Thank you for seeing me
on such short notice, Judge.

09:29.177 --> 09:30.744
RICHARDS:
Of course.

09:30.787 --> 09:32.528
Elaine said you have
something on the mill murders.

09:32.572 --> 09:35.139
TRASK:
Yeah, a confidential informant

09:35.183 --> 09:38.360
linked some mill activity to
the night the blood was found.

09:38.403 --> 09:41.102
RICHARDS:
Well, the mill's over here,

09:41.145 --> 09:42.407
murders are over there.

09:42.451 --> 09:44.409
Uh, what's the link
between the two?

09:44.453 --> 09:46.629
Well, my informant told me
a suspicious shipment

09:46.673 --> 09:49.676
will be in the mill tomorrow
and then it'll be gone.

09:49.719 --> 09:50.894
It's now or never.

09:50.938 --> 09:52.200
RICHARDS:
Okay, Pete, but, I mean,

09:52.243 --> 09:53.244
a blood trail
leading to the mill?

09:53.288 --> 09:54.637
TRASK:
I know,

09:54.681 --> 09:56.421
I know, but I need warrants
to search the mill

09:56.465 --> 09:58.815
and get DNA samples
from the employees.

09:58.859 --> 10:01.644
I expect us to find
the link then.

10:01.688 --> 10:03.646
:
I won't tell if you won't.

10:03.690 --> 10:04.908
RICHARDS:
Elaine!

10:08.085 --> 10:09.609
Need a warrant, Judge?

10:09.652 --> 10:12.481
Okay, people,
we're going in tomorrow.

10:12.524 --> 10:14.962
3:00 p.m. sharp
with the state CSI team.

10:15.005 --> 10:17.921
They'll do their black light
magic, but it's on us

10:17.965 --> 10:19.923
to ask for DNA swabs.

10:19.967 --> 10:22.143
Now Rook here,
fresh from the academy,

10:22.186 --> 10:24.536
is gonna explain the latest
rules on how to ask.

10:24.580 --> 10:26.887
Say what's on this card,
only what's on this card,

10:26.930 --> 10:30.412
and remember,
no matter what they answer...

10:30.455 --> 10:32.153
you say "thank you."

10:32.196 --> 10:34.285
Any questions?

10:34.329 --> 10:36.723
JAKE:
This is me.

10:39.203 --> 10:41.771
No "ta

10:41.815 --> 10:44.034
Ta-da.

10:47.777 --> 10:49.518
It's cute.

10:49.561 --> 10:51.259
I told you I didn't want
to come back here.

10:51.302 --> 10:53.565
:
I was being serious.

10:53.609 --> 10:55.045
Yeah, I'm just gonna...

10:55.089 --> 10:57.352
I could offer you
coffee, but, uh,

10:57.395 --> 11:00.834
I was thinking maybe we'd go up
the street for an iced coffee?

11:00.877 --> 11:03.706
You don't have
to offer me anything.

11:03.750 --> 11:05.447
Lunch was perfect.

11:05.490 --> 11:07.318
I thought it'd be
weird, going on a date

11:07.362 --> 11:08.929
in the daytime.

11:08.972 --> 11:10.931
But it was nice.

11:10.974 --> 11:12.889
It kind of felt like
we were skipping school.

11:12.933 --> 11:15.370
You know, bakers, we, uh,

11:15.413 --> 11:18.590
we do things just
the same as everyone else,

11:18.634 --> 11:21.071
we just do it
when the sun is up.

11:21.115 --> 11:23.117
Hmm.

11:38.132 --> 11:40.395
I wasn't sure if I was
reading you right.

11:40.438 --> 11:42.353
Oh, you were.

11:51.188 --> 11:54.148
Bedroom?Uh, that's my office.

11:54.191 --> 11:57.455
Uh, we're in the bedroom.

11:57.499 --> 11:59.196
You sleep on the couch?

11:59.240 --> 12:01.372
You making fun of me,
sleeping on the couch

12:01.416 --> 12:04.114
I don't really care
where you sleep.

12:04.158 --> 12:07.161
I just want to know
where you fuck.

12:24.221 --> 12:25.832
I got it.

12:32.752 --> 12:35.319
Hey, Elaine.

12:35.363 --> 12:38.409
Uh, sorry, Bud. I didn't mean
to come by unannounced,

12:38.453 --> 12:40.847
but the police chief came by
Judge Richardson's chamber.

12:40.890 --> 12:42.674
BUD: Why don't we get you
in out of the heat, okay?

12:42.718 --> 12:43.850
ELAINE:
Ah, thank you.

12:43.893 --> 12:45.634
I'm wilting.

12:45.677 --> 12:46.809
Are you, uh, thirsty?

12:46.853 --> 12:49.159
ELAINE:
Sure.

12:49.203 --> 12:50.639
BUD :
Um...

12:51.945 --> 12:53.642
Elaine, this is Jenny Ludlow.

12:53.685 --> 12:55.818
Jenny does some work for me
around the house.

12:55.862 --> 12:58.865
Uh, could you, uh, get Ms.
Carlton a glass of water?

12:58.908 --> 13:01.432
I recognize you from somewhere.

13:01.476 --> 13:03.826
Where do I know you from

13:05.306 --> 13:07.612
I clean a lot of places
around town.

13:07.656 --> 13:10.528
: Well, you
got a good one here.

13:10.572 --> 13:13.009
Bud pretty much singlehandedly
saved my family.

13:13.053 --> 13:15.011
All right, let's not
get into all that.

13:15.055 --> 13:16.534
ELAINE: He never
changes, does he?

13:16.578 --> 13:19.233
Mr. Carl's very humble.

13:19.276 --> 13:23.367
Um, let's talk in the office?

13:23.411 --> 13:25.195
Uh, nice to
meet you, Jenny.

13:25.239 --> 13:28.024
Nice to meet you.

13:28.068 --> 13:31.201
You know, I would
lose my job

13:31.245 --> 13:32.768
if the judge knew
I was here?

13:32.812 --> 13:35.118
Let's talk downstairs, okay?

13:40.036 --> 13:42.517
Uh, white noise machine.
And that

13:42.560 --> 13:44.736
sort of emits, like,
the right kind of light

13:44.780 --> 13:46.608
and sound waves and shit.

13:46.651 --> 13:50.133
Sounds like you doubt
the science.

13:50.177 --> 13:52.483
I got a sleep metronome.

13:52.527 --> 13:53.920
Self-cooling pillow.

13:53.963 --> 13:56.444
Earplugs.
Shit on my phone.

13:56.487 --> 13:59.751
Been to the doctors,
therapists, acupuncturists.

13:59.795 --> 14:00.970
When did it start?

14:01.014 --> 14:03.190
What do you mean, start?

14:03.233 --> 14:05.540
I mean, when was the last time
you slept well?

14:07.020 --> 14:08.717
About a year ago.

14:08.760 --> 14:11.285
What happened then?

14:16.290 --> 14:18.466
Do you have nightmares?

14:18.509 --> 14:20.642
You got to sleep
to have nightmares.

14:20.685 --> 14:25.299
I close my eyes and get, like...

14:25.342 --> 14:28.911
Did something terrible happen
in that bedroom back there?

14:28.955 --> 14:31.566
Man, you really want to see
what's in the bedroom, huh?

14:31.609 --> 14:33.220
All right.

14:33.263 --> 14:35.048
Go ahead.

14:43.665 --> 14:46.494
Is this all one case?Uh-huh.

14:46.537 --> 14:49.497
A missing little girl
named Abby Washington.

14:49.540 --> 14:52.935
You may be a
little... obsessive.

14:52.979 --> 14:55.068
Nah, I just
got drunk last night

14:55.111 --> 14:56.983
and wanted to make it look
like I'm a real detective.

15:09.343 --> 15:12.259
BUD:
It's always good to catch up.ELAINE: Yes.

15:12.302 --> 15:14.739
Let's not make it so long
between visits next time.

15:14.783 --> 15:17.220
You bet.

15:17.264 --> 15:18.526
Thanks, Elaine.

15:18.569 --> 15:20.615
ELAINE:
Buddy.

15:54.127 --> 15:55.780
Hey, it's me.

15:55.824 --> 15:59.567
You know that shipment
to Vancouver we talked about?

15:59.610 --> 16:01.873
Yeah.

16:01.917 --> 16:04.485
Hold it aside.

16:04.528 --> 16:07.618
There's something
I'm fixing to put in it.

16:07.662 --> 16:10.534
Yeah, thanks, Walsh.

17:03.631 --> 17:06.895
You want to talk about it?

17:06.938 --> 17:09.941
Are you stressed 'cause
of the Seven Bloods thing?

17:13.597 --> 17:15.208
I've been thinking
about how you told me

17:15.251 --> 17:18.298
all that stuff about your wife.

17:18.341 --> 17:20.517
About losing your wife.

17:20.561 --> 17:23.694
How much that
must weigh on you.

17:23.738 --> 17:25.522
I've been thinking
about you...

17:26.784 --> 17:30.484
...in this big house
by yourself.

17:35.315 --> 17:37.926
It's... roasting out here.

17:37.969 --> 17:40.233
Had the AC on

17:40.276 --> 17:42.931
full blast all day.

17:44.585 --> 17:46.587
Nothing helps.

17:48.023 --> 17:50.330
I like the heat.

17:50.373 --> 17:53.637
When I was in foster
care, we didn't have AC

17:53.681 --> 17:55.248
in the house.

17:55.291 --> 17:57.424
It'd be two, three of us
to a room,

17:57.467 --> 18:00.992
lying there late at night,
sweating in our little beds.

18:01.036 --> 18:04.474
One girl, little older
than me, she said

18:04.518 --> 18:08.478
we should pretend we were
lying on the beach,

18:08.522 --> 18:11.873
wearing suntan lotion.

18:11.916 --> 18:14.789
Pretty funny, 'cause none of us
ever seen the ocean.

18:17.008 --> 18:20.360
You ever do anything
like that?

18:20.403 --> 18:22.013
Like what?

18:22.057 --> 18:25.800
Imagine you're somewhere else?

18:25.843 --> 18:28.846
I don't.

18:31.022 --> 18:34.983
Not sure what would be here
once I got back, I guess.

18:44.993 --> 18:47.169
I didn't finish the upstairs,

18:47.213 --> 18:51.434
and I decided I'm gonna make
some meals for you.

18:51.478 --> 18:54.220
You don't have to do that.No.

18:54.263 --> 18:56.526
Got to eat something
home-cooked every now and then.

18:56.570 --> 18:57.788
I'll be back tomorrow.

18:57.832 --> 18:59.616
Okay if I leave my supplies out?

18:59.660 --> 19:01.662
Of course.

19:04.752 --> 19:06.754
Get some rest, Mr. Carl.

19:26.382 --> 19:28.515
Shit. You scared
the shit out of me.

19:28.558 --> 19:30.560
I'm sorry.

19:37.132 --> 19:39.439
So, what
are we watching?

19:39.482 --> 19:42.050
Oh, it's nothing. It's stupid.

19:43.094 --> 19:44.879
Yeah, you're-you're allowed

19:44.922 --> 19:46.489
to turn the sound on.

19:46.533 --> 19:48.709
I-I know.

19:48.752 --> 19:50.798
I, uh, I just don't
want to wake her up.

19:50.841 --> 19:53.844
No, she's out usually
until, like, 5:00.

19:53.888 --> 19:56.151
She wakes you up at 5:00?

19:56.195 --> 19:57.848
Sometimes.

19:57.892 --> 19:59.546
I don't know
how you do it.

19:59.589 --> 20:02.113
I mean, I'm tired
